 ## 12. What Thedi can adopt from Yutori
 
+### 12.1 Two-Week Sprint Plan (Next 14 Days)
+
+**Goal:** Close the trust gap and enable multi-channel delivery before Yutori's next feature drop.
+
+| Priority | Action | Yutori Section | Est. Effort | Owner |
+|---|---|---|---|---|
+| **P0** | **Ship User-Visible Audit Trail** — Add a "View Scout Run" modal to the digest email footer and web dashboard. Show: pages visited, filters applied, reasoning chain, rejected candidates. | 2.4 Audit trail | 3 days | Eng |
+| **P1** | **Enable Reply-to-Refine** — Wire inbound email replies to `scout-feedback-submit` endpoint. Parse user text as prompt adjustment for next run. | 3. Delivery channels | 2 days | Eng |
+| **P1** | **Add Webhook Delivery** — Allow users to configure a webhook URL per scout. Emit JSON payload on match. | 3. Delivery channels | 2 days | Eng |
+| **P2** | **Cost Transparency Badge** — Display token/compute cost per digest in the email footer and dashboard. | 2.5 Cost transparency | 1 day | Eng |
+| **P2** | **Starter Scout Templates** — On signup, show 5 pre-built scouts (News, Research, Price, Launch, Mention) with one-click "Create". | 6. Scout types | 1 day | Design |
+
+**Why these first?**
+- Audit trail is Yutori's **trust primitive** — we must match it to avoid being seen as a "black box".
+- Reply-to-refine is **low-lift UX win** that leverages existing email infrastructure.
+- Webhooks enable **programmatic downstream** (Zapier, custom code) — critical for power users.
+- Cost transparency builds **pricing trust** before we scale usage.
+- Templates reduce **onboarding friction** — Yutori's "one prompt box" is simpler than our form.
+
+**What to skip for now:**
+- Authenticated connectors (Gmail, Slack, Notion) — P2, requires OAuth infra.
+- NL-to-structured scout parsing — P3, we already have form-based creation.
+- iOS app — P3, web dashboard + email is sufficient for MVP.
+- Live Artifacts — P3, not core to research digest use case.
+
+**Success metrics for 2 weeks:**
+- 80% of active users view audit trail at least once.
+- 30% of users enable webhook delivery.
+- 50% reduction in "why did you send this?" support tickets.
+- 20% increase in scout creation rate (due to templates).
+
